description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust Staff Bank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this is a Bank/Temporary advert to join the Temporary Staffing Bank&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Staff Bank Department is a dedicated team aiming to provide a quality service to Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust. The Staff Bank strives to support our Hospitals with competent, reliable and registered Staff Nurses who will be able to provide the highest level of service to our patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are absolutely committed to ensuring that our patients have the best possible experience within our hospitals. We seek people who are committed to delivering outstanding patient care, whatever their role, and who take pride in what they do. We place a high value on treating all patients, visitors and colleagues with respect and dignity, and seek people who strive for excellence in all that they do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Join our staff bank and be a valued member of the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Bank Band 6 Dietitian&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; To provide a specialist dietetic service to medical, surgical and critical care in-patient beds, or outpatient clinics, across the Trust in liaison with the Clinical Lead Dietitian.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Imperial Staff Bank are seeking a Band 6 Dietitian; however we welcome band 5 applicants aspiring to band 6 roles, or new band 7’s that would be happy with band 6 work. Suitable applicants must have a minimum of 6 months hospital based experience as a Dietician and be able to commit to a line of work (Monday – Friday 09.00 – 17.00). Rate of pay for Band 5 in £19.01 and includes holiday pay (WTR), Band 6 is £23.33 including holiday pay (WTR). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have roles available at St Mary’s Hospital, Charing Cross Hospital and Hammersmith Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and dynamic registered Dietitians to support our large, high profile, friendly Nutrition and Dietetic service within the Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be responsible for the delivery of a high quality, evidence-based clinical services within medicine, surgery and intensive care environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To perform dietetic assessment of patients with diverse presentations and complex physical and psychological conditions, to develop and deliver individualised interventions and discharge plans where required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please apply if you have excellent dietetic knowledge, have the ability to prioritise your workload, enjoy working within a dynamic team and can work under pressure we look forward to receiving your application for consideration. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate of Pay:&lt;/strong&gt; £19.01 - £23.33 per hour depending on band (including WTR) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations: &lt;/strong&gt;Roles available inSt Mary’s Hospital, Charing Cross Hospital and Hammersmith Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 6 months of hospital based experience as a Dietitian.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HCPC registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear enhanced DBS or willing to complete requirements to obtain a DBS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to prioritise work load in a pressured environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to perform dietetic assessments and deliver discharge plans when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good team working and interpersonal skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Bank shifts is easy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value all of our staff and aim to provide rewarding careers and benefits, fulfilling work environments and exciting opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits for you:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great Opportunity to progress within the Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekly Payments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holiday pay included in hourly rate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive Pay Rates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Platform to gain experience in different areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Friendly team environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Efficient Recruitment Process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Complimentary Mandatory Training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust was launched on 1st October, 2007. Made up of five hospitals; Charing Cross, Hammersmith, Queen Charlotte&#39;s and Chelsea, St Mary&#39;s and the Western Eye, and integrating with Imperial College London, we are one of the largest acute trusts in the UK with an annual turnover exceeding £900 million and employing almost 10,000 staff. Offering more than 50 clinical specialities, and with one of the largest portfolios of services in the country we have one million patient contacts a year.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Trust has established the UK’s first Academic Health Science Centre (AHSC). The AHSC aims to bring together the delivery of healthcare services, teaching and research in a partnership for the purpose of improving the health of its patients, advancing clinical teaching and scientific invention and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust Values&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an organisation we expect everyone to be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kind&lt;br /&gt; We are considerate and thoughtful, so you feel respected and included.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We put people first&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We listen, notice and respond&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We see things from others’ point of view&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notice when someone needs help&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make eye contact and smile&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Introduce ourselves by name and role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actively listen and respond to others&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make time for meaningful interactions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative&lt;br /&gt; We actively seek others’ views and ideas, so we achieve more together.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work as a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re open and approachable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re adaptable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert&lt;br /&gt; We draw on our diverse skills, knowledge and experience, so we provide the best possible care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re informed and up to date&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re reliable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re responsible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aspirational&lt;br /&gt; We are receptive and responsive to new thinking, so we never stop learning, discovering and improving.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strive for excellence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We embrace innovation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We champion better care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact a friendly member of our recruitment team on &lt;strong&gt;0203 311 1552&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;imperial.staffbank.ahp@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;IMPORTANT:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure you check your emails regularly as this is how we will communicate with you throughout the recruitment process. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note that due to a high volume of applications, if you have not been contacted in two weeks your application has been unsuccessful.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
